{
  "number": 2519,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2519",
  "title": "Add allItems template option to InifiniteHits",
  "body": "The infiniteHits widget is almost at feature parity with the hits widget, with the exception of the [allItems template option](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/infiniteHits.html#struct-InfiniteHitsTemplates).\r\n\r\nThis means using tabular data with infiniteHits requires either using a connector (more verbose) or, if using a front-end framework e.g. Bootstrap or Materialize) a bunch of extra markup to convert tables to an instantsearch-friendly structure.\r\n\r\nMy use case:\r\nI'd like to use hits widget + pagination on desktop, but infinite scroll on mobile\r\n\r\nOther use cases:\r\nEnterprise'y customers using Tableau ([example](http://www.centralvalleycf.org/nonprofits/grants-overview/grants/))\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
